    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-05-09T17:52:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-05-09T17:52:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <head>155. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d155fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 962A.7162B/5–855. Secret. Drafted by Blumberg, cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_LCB1">Lyon</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName>. Repeated to Bonn and
                        London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-05-09T17:52:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1955—5:52 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tosec 7. For <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d155fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> was in Paris for the meeting
                        of the North Atlantic Council, May 9–11.</note> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName>. We are proceeding Washington approach
                    British and French re possible use force contemplated <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5404/1,<note n="3" xml:id="d155fn3">See <ref
                            target="frus1952-54v07p2#pg_1390">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations,</hi>, 1952–1954, vol. VII, Part 2,
                            p. 1390</ref>.</note> which was deferred pending ratification Paris
                    Agreements. Will use current Autobahn situation as introduction (re <gloss
                        target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 2, rptd Bonn 846, London 1110).<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d155fn4">
                        <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 2 reported that
                            <persName>Dulles</persName> had approved an approach to the British and
                        French with regard to Berlin. (Department of State, Central Files,
                        962A.7162A/5–855)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Meanwhile, we hopeful dispatch instructions Bonn today re Autobahn situation
                    which envisage Allied and German planning in event approaches Soviets
                    unproductive. This would include use military facilities for which we are
                    seeking Defense approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
